you can, okay, so --

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:53.480
I don't doubt that
book's being challenged.

00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:55.640
That book -- I mean,
as far as my books go,

00:20:55.640 --> 00:20:57.720
as far as content goes,
that one goes as far,

00:20:57.720 --> 00:21:00.880
if you don't know what "Tricks"
is, it deals and the sequel

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:03.070
"Traffick," they deal

00:21:03.070 --> 00:21:04.780
with domestic minor
sex trafficking,

00:21:04.780 --> 00:21:07.860
so teen prostitution.

00:21:07.860 --> 00:21:11.250
You could start a petition.

00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:14.880
I can give you letters--
Like if you email me,

00:21:14.880 --> 00:21:17.990
I can send you letters
from readers about why

00:21:17.990 --> 00:21:20.770
that book is important to
them, what it meant to them,

00:21:20.770 --> 00:21:22.210
how it helped them through.

00:21:22.210 --> 00:21:27.470
And for me, I wanted to explore
teen prostitution because I live

00:21:27.470 --> 00:21:33.210
in Reno and there was an
FBI bust there, a big raid.

00:21:33.210 --> 00:21:36.860
They came in and
they took 23 kids,

00:21:36.860 --> 00:21:40.700
all under the age of 12, out.

00:21:40.700 --> 00:21:45.850
And so domestic minor sex
trafficking, the average age,

00:21:45.850 --> 00:21:48.130
the average age of a
young person trafficked

00:21:48.130 --> 00:21:49.430
in is 12 years old.

00:21:49.430 --> 00:21:50.740
That's the average age.

00:21:50.740 --> 00:21:56.400
So it's important that we
understand possible victims,

00:21:56.400 --> 00:22:01.280
like shopping mall kids who
like could be victimized easily,

00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:04.410
what perpetrators look like.

00:22:04.410 --> 00:22:08.340
I just had an article come
out in "VOYA Magazine"

00:22:08.340 --> 00:22:12.430
and the big thing is libraries
are now one of the places

00:22:12.430 --> 00:22:16.190
that the traffickers
target because they look

00:22:16.190 --> 00:22:17.730
for vulnerable kids and a lot

00:22:17.730 --> 00:22:19.810
of vulnerable kids
end up in libraries.

00:22:19.810 --> 00:22:22.450
So that might be a
way of looking at it,

00:22:22.450 --> 00:22:24.500
of approaching them as well.

00:22:24.500 --> 00:22:27.340
In fact, if you -- I can
send you that article

00:22:27.340 --> 00:22:29.770
and it might be interesting for
your librarian to look at it

00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:32.770
and read it because "VOYA" is
very much involved with trying

00:22:32.770 --> 00:22:35.690
to change that as part of that.

00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:36.990
